---

Thoroughly shake @coconut milk{1%unit} in container before opening.

In a #small pot{}, combine @water{1/2%cup}, @coconut milk{1/4%cup}, @butter{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and @salt{pinch} (for 4 servings, use 1 cup water, 1⁄2 cup coconut milk, 2 TBSP butter, and 2 tsp sugar). (Be sure to measure the coconut milk—we sent more!)

Bring to a boil, then stir in @white rice{1/2%cup}. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until liquid has absorbed and rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim @scallions{2}(trimmed) and cut whites into 1-inch pieces and thinly slice greens. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

== Sautéed Cabbage & Scallions ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%oz} and scallion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; taste and season with @salt{} if desired. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside until ready to serve. Wipe out pan.>

> To cook more than four servings, use 1 cup water, 1⁄2 cup coconut milk, 2 TBSP butter, and 2 tsp sugar for the rice.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season lightly with @salt{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for cabbage over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If chicken starts to brown too quickly, reduce heat and cover.

== Jerk Sauce ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @jerk sauce{4%tbsp}, @water{2%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp} (4 TBSP water and 1⁄2 tsp sugar for 4 servings).

Reduce heat to low and stir jerk sauce mixture into pan with chicken. Cook, covered, until sauce has slightly reduced, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add another splash of water.

== To Serve ==

Fluff coconut rice with a #fork{}; stir in as much lime zest as you like.

Divide coconut rice, chicken, and cabbage between plates in separate sections. Top chicken with jerk pan sauce, scallion greens, and a squeeze of lime juice. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.